<archetype>
  <archetypetitle>Second Son</archetypetitle>
  <archetypeid>second_son</archetypeid>
  <archetypedescription>           
    <p>
      Second sons are extranumenary young nobles, the product of too much money and not
      enough to do.  Indolent nare-do-wells roaming the lands, living off their wits
      and their quick reactions, looking for adventure and a handfull of silver
      whereever they might find it.  On occassion they make a name for themselves,
      and possibly a fortune, if they are lucky.  More often their lot is an early grave.
    </p>

    <figure>
      <img src="./resources/rake/caleb_the_witch_hunter__second_take_by_solidtom-d5v025x.jpg" scale="0.8"/>
    </figure>    
  </archetypedescription>

  
  <archetypeprimaryabilities>
      <list> 
        <li>Str:+1, End:-1, Ag:+1, Spd:+0, Per:+0, or</li>
        <li>Str:+1, End:+0, Ag:+0, Spd:+0, Per:+0</li>
      </list>
  </archetypeprimaryabilities>
  <archetypeinitialabilities>
    <p>
      All Second Sons start with the following skills: ✱sword.strike_2, Sword Parry I, ✱physical.dodge_1, 
      ✱social.etiquette[Westreich-Nobility]_3, ✱language.merovingian_4, ✱luck.lucky_3, I Think I'm OK I, ✱luck.nick_of_time_1,
      ✱lore.book_learning_1, and ✱transport.horse_riding_1.
    </p>
    
  </archetypeinitialabilities>  
  <archetypemovedistance>6</archetypemovedistance>
  <startingcash>50 + 2d4 gp</startingcash>
  <startinggear>Leather armour, long sword, Fine cloak, fine clothes, leather belt, dagger, rations for a week.</startinggear>

  <height>
    <metric>170 + 3d10 cm</metric> 
    <imperial>5'4" + 2d6 inches</imperial>
  </height>
  <weight>
    <metric>60 + 2d8 kg</metric> 
    <imperial>130 + 4d20 pounds</imperial>
  </weight>
  <age>18 + 1d8 years</age>

  <aspectexamples>Life is Short, In for a Penny in for a Noble, Time For A Quick Hand of Cards, As My Daddy Used to
  Say..,  There Is Always Time to Be A Gentleman, Fortune Favours the Bold!</aspectexamples>
  <archetypetags>
    <human/>
    <humanoid/>    
    <medium/>
  </archetypetags>

  <archetypebio>

    <subsection>
      <subsectiontitle>Origin</subsectiontitle>
      <p>
    	Determine where the character came from by rolling once on the Homeland table below.
      </p>
          
      <table>
      	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
      	<tablespec>
      	  <fixed>0.94</fixed>
      	</tablespec>
      	<tabletitle>Homelands</tabletitle>

      	<tableheaderrow>
      	  <td>Homeland - Roll 1D12 </td>
      	</tableheaderrow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td><bold>1-2 Almaignee</bold>: ✱social.adversary[Greenskins]_1, ✱social.adversary[Giants]_1,
	  ✱social.etiquette[Almaignee]_3</td>
      	</tablerow>
	
      	<tablerow>
      	  <td><bold>3-4 Albion</bold>: ✱language.hybernian_1, ✱social.etiquette[Albion]_3, ✱social.etiquette[Hybernia]_1,
	  ✱social.contacts[Albion]_1, ✱social.adversary[Greenskins]_1</td>
      	</tablerow>
	
      	<tablerow>
      	  <td><bold>5-11 Westreich</bold>: ✱social.etiquette[Westreich]_3, ✱social.contacts[Westreich]_2</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td><bold>12 Choose</bold></td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablelabel>table:{{ doc_name }}-homeland</tablelabel>
      </table>
    </subsection>

    <subsection>
      <subsectiontitle>Upbringing Tables</subsectiontitle>      
      <p>
    	Roll on once on one of the following table.
      </p>      
      
      <table>
    	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
    	<tablespec>
    	  <fixed>0.18</fixed>
    	  <fixed>0.71</fixed>
    	</tablespec>
    	<tabletitle>Study I</tabletitle>

    	<tableheaderrow>
    	  <td>Roll 1D12</td>
    	  <td>Study</td>
    	</tableheaderrow>
	
    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>1-2</td>
    	  <td>✱transport.horse_riding_2, ✱physical.rest_2, ✱physical.grapple_2 or ✱physical.head_butt_2, ✱physical.punch_2 or ✱physical.throw_2</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>3-4</td>
    	  <td>✱physical.listen_2, ✱transport.horse_riding_2 or ✱wilderness.wayfinding_1, ✱physical.sure_feet_2 or ✱physical.jump_2, ✱social.intimidate_2 or ✱social.negotiate_2</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>5-6</td>
    	  <td>✱wilderness.survivalism_1, ✱social.rally_2, ✱physical.sleep_2 or ✱physical.rest_1, ✱skulduggery.sneak_2 or ✱physical.charge_2</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>7-8</td>
    	  <td>✱wilderness.scout_1, ✱physical.notice_2, ✱physical.charge_2 or ✱physical.dodge_2, ✱physical.climb_1 or ✱physical.swim_2, ✱arts.singing_2</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>9-10</td>
    	  <td>✱transport.horse_riding_2, ✱transport.animal_handling_1, ✱physical.juggernaut_2, ✱physical.move_2 or ✱physical.charge_2, ✱physical.punch_2</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>11-12</td>
    	  <td>Choose one of the above</td>
    	</tablerow>
	
    	<tablelabel>table:{{ doc_name }}-study-i</tablelabel>
      </table>
    </subsection>


    <subsection>
      <subsectiontitle>Training Tables</subsectiontitle>      
      <p>
    	Roll once on each of the following tables.
      </p>      
      
      <table>
    	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
    	<tablespec>
    	  <fixed>0.18</fixed>
    	  <fixed>0.71</fixed>
    	</tablespec>
    	<tabletitle>Study I</tabletitle>

    	<tableheaderrow>
    	  <td>Roll 1D12</td>
    	  <td>Study</td>
    	</tableheaderrow>
	
    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>1-2</td>
    	  <td>✱arts.lore_3,
	  One of ✱lore.history[Westenreich]_3 or ✱lore.politics[Westenreich]_2,
	  One of ✱physical.kick_1 or ✱physical.grapple_1.
	  One of ✱physical.dodge_2 or ✱skulduggery.cloak_fighting_3.</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>3-4</td>
    	  <td>✱arts.oratory_3,
	  One of ✱lore.history[Aquilonia]_3 or ✱lore.history[Averoigne]_3,
	  One of ✱physical.run_2 or ✱physical.sure_feet_1.
	  One of ✱physical.dodge_2 or ✱skulduggery.cloak_fighting_3.
	  </td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>5-6</td>
    	  <td>✱language.poitevin_3,
	  One of ✱lore.natural_history_2 or ✱lore.mathematics_2,
	  ✱archery.shoot_2 or (✱gun.shoot_2 and ✱gun.maintenance_2),
	  One of ✱physical.kick_1 or ✱physical.grapple_1.
	  </td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>7-8</td>
    	  <td>✱language.aquilonian_2,
	  One of ✱lore.history[Albion]_2 or ✱lore.history[Hibernia]_2,
	  One of ✱dagger.strike_3 or ✱archery.shoot_2.
	  One of ✱physical.dodge_2 or ✱skulduggery.cloak_fighting_3.
	  One of ✱physical.kick_1 or ✱physical.grapple_1.
	  </td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>9-10</td>
    	  <td>✱lore.law[Westenreich]_2,
	  One of ✱lore.history[Aquilonia]_3 or ✱lore.politics[Westenreich]_2.
	  ✱sword.strike_3 and one of ✱sword.feint_1 or ✱sword.parry_2.
	  One of ✱physical.kick_1 or ✱physical.grapple_1.
	  </td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>11-12</td>
    	  <td>Choose one of the above</td>
    	</tablerow>
	
    	<tablelabel>table:{{ doc_name }}-study-i</tablelabel>
      </table>


      <table>
    	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
    	<tablespec>
    	  <fixed>0.18</fixed>
    	  <fixed>0.71</fixed>
    	</tablespec>
    	<tabletitle>Study 2</tabletitle>

    	<tableheaderrow>
    	  <td>Roll 1D12</td>
    	  <td>Study</td>
    	</tableheaderrow>
	
    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>1-2</td>
    	  <td>Choose one of ✱physical.listen_1 or ✱physical.notice_1.  ✱skulduggery.concealment_2 or ✱skulduggery.pick_locks_1</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>3-4</td>
    	  <td>Choose one of ✱skulduggery.disguise_1 or ✱physical.climb_1. One of ✱social.leadership_1 or ✱social.fame[Westenreich]_3</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>5-6</td>
    	  <td>✱physical.jump_2, Choose one of ✱physical.move_1 or ✱physical.run_1, One of ✱social.leadership_1 or ✱physical.dodge_2 or ✱archery.shoot_1</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>7-8</td>
    	  <td>One of ✱physical.swim_3 or ✱physical.charge_1, One of ✱skulduggery.ropecraft_2 or ✱skulduggery.sneak_1</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>9-10</td>
    	  <td>Choose one of ✱physical.knockout_1 or ✱physical.punch_1.  One of ✱skulduggery.sleight_of_hand_1 or ✱social.negotiate_1</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>11-12</td>
    	  <td>Choose one of the above</td>
    	</tablerow>
	
    	<tablelabel>table:{{ doc_name }}-study-ii</tablelabel>
      </table>
    </subsection>
      

    <subsection>
      <subsectiontitle>Youth</subsectiontitle>
      <p>
	Now work out the character's backgroun in their youth by rolling once on the
	Nature table below.
      </p>
      
      <table>
      	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
      	<tablespec>
      	  <fixed>0.18</fixed>
      	  <fixed>0.71</fixed>
      	</tablespec>
      	<tabletitle>Nature</tabletitle>

      	<tableheaderrow>
      	  <td>Roll 1D12</td>
      	  <td>Birth</td>
      	</tableheaderrow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td>1-2</td>
      	  <td><bold>Sterner Stuff</bold>: Mettle Pool +1d</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td>3-4</td>
      	  <td><bold>Fortunate</bold>: Luck Pool +1d</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td>5-6</td>
      	  <td><bold>Stout</bold>: Endurance+1</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td>7</td>
      	  <td><bold>Observant</bold>: Perception+1</td>
      	</tablerow>
	
      	<tablerow>
      	  <td>8</td>
      	  <td><bold>Deft</bold>: Agile+1</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td>9</td>
      	  <td><bold>Fast</bold>: Speed+1</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td>10</td>
      	  <td><bold>Strong</bold>: Strength+1</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td>11</td>
      	  <td><bold>Reroll</bold> d10 twice (Reroll duplicates)</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td>12</td>
      	  <td><bold>Reroll</bold> d10 and Pick<leqsymbol/>10 (No duplicates)</td>
      	</tablerow>
	
      	<tablelabel>table:{{ doc_name }}-nature</tablelabel>
      </table>
      
      <p>
	See what the characters fortune holds.
      </p>
      
      <table>
    	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
    	<tablespec>
    	  <fixed>0.18</fixed>
    	  <fixed>0.71</fixed>
    	</tablespec>
    	<tabletitle>Fortune</tabletitle>

    	<tableheaderrow>
    	  <td>Roll 1D12</td>
    	  <td>Fortune</td>
    	</tableheaderrow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>1-2</td>
    	  <td>Bicorne Hat, Wax Candles, Sack, Wineskin, Book - Tales of Heroes</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>3</td>
    	  <td>Cossack Hat, Cashmere Sash, Leather Purse, Hip Flask</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>4-5</td>
    	  <td>Cavalier Hat, Rope <measurement><imperial>60'</imperial><metric>20m</metric></measurement>,
    	  Paper and ink</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>6-7</td>
    	  <td>Kettle, Book of Poetry</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>8-9</td>
    	  <td>Cavalier Hat, Tin Cup, Scarf</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>10</td>
    	  <td>Playing Cards, Small Pot</td>
    	</tablerow>

    	<tablerow>
    	  <td>11-12</td>
    	  <td>Choose</td>
    	</tablerow>
	
    	<tablelabel>table:{{ doc_name }}-fortune</tablelabel>
      </table>
    </subsection>      
  </archetypebio>



  
